HEADWORD: Horometry
<hw>Ho*rom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>horom⟦eacute⟧trie</ets>. See <er>Horometer</er>.]</ety> <def>The
art, practice, or method of measuring time by hours and subordinate
divisions.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>horometry</xex> of antiquity.⟦rdquo⟧
